>>44731601
>I'm personally heavily biased against romantic drama of any kind given how it almost always feels like padding
That's where you and I differ, because I love romantic drama/conflict. I think there's something inherently compelling about putting in the work to fix a flawed relationship, and I think that kind of drama is sorely lacking from a lot of stories here. Some amount of disagreement and argument is necessary for a healthy partnership, and even the happiest couples get into fights over stupid shit once in a while. Sometimes we say things that hurt each other on accident, sometimes we do it on purpose because we're frustrated. I think it makes for both good and realistic romance when two people can move past that and come out with a stronger bond.
But I also used to like Grey's Anatomy, so what do I know?
